Here is my suggestion for semantic interface regardining the context bus. The operations represent a ContextEventPattern with the format [S,P,O] defining the filters on each proeprty of the event. Asterisk * means no restriction. For simplicity, I would ommit restrictions on other properties such as e.g. timestamp. Additional operations can be added in this format representing additional ContextEventPatterns passed as filter.

The collaboration with the Context Subscriber semantic interface of CHE is a bit special, because it gets events from all sources, and that shouldnt be represented on the diagram. However, maybe other components have more specific subscribers and it may make sense to link publishers that publish such events to those interfaces... A stereoptype with <<ContextEvent>> could suffice but then we have the same question of how to specify which Event Pattern is this event matching... although here it is not so important.
